keyValuePair.Value: Are you confident you'll win it today?
You've had a fantastic season and here you are, going into the last game, knowing a win will see your boys clinch the title. Feeling confident? Will the boys finish the job?
The lads are only thinking one thing.
The team's been great to be around this season. I look at our qualities, like team-work, positivity and determination, and I'm sure the lads will go out and do what they need to do today.
The team's been great to be around this season. I look at our qualities, like team-work, positivity and determination, and I'm sure the lads will go out and do what they need to do today.
It's a cup final!
We've worked hard all season and now it's down to what we can do in one game. This is our cup final. The boys are out to prove that they're winners.
We'll try to keep our heads.
Look, it's exciting. It's emotional. It's a massive occasion for the club. But the boys have to put all that to one side and focus on the job in hand: getting the three points that we need.
Can the boys do it today?
Just one game to go. And one point from it will be enough to see your team finish top. These are exciting times for the club. Will the team clinch the title today?
We deserve it.
I can't speak highly enough of the players. They've achieved remarkable things together this season. I think we've been the best team and I'm confident we'll set the seal on that today.
We'll want to do it with a win.
A point will be enough to win the title but that won't be enough for the boys. We've been positive every game this season and that won't change today. We want to sign off with a win.
We mustn't let it slip now.
We're very close but we can't afford to be complacent today. We respect %1s and mustn't give them the chance to spoil the party. We know there's still work to be done.
What a way to win the title!
What a way to win the title!
Incredible drama! The team did the club and your fans proud today, getting the win you needed to see you crowned champions. What does this achievement mean to you and the players?
Incredible drama! The team did the club and your fans proud today, getting the win you needed to see you crowned champions. What does this achievement mean to you and the players?
I'm delighted for everyone!
The boys have been brave and resilient all season and those are the qualities that got us over the line today. I'm happy for the club and the fans, and I'm very proud of the players.
The boys have been brave and resilient all season and those are the qualities that got us over the line today. I'm happy for the club and the fans, and I'm very proud of the players.
I hope this is just the start for us.
A great result and a great season. But the mark of true champions is to always be looking forward to the next challenge. This is just the start. I know we can be even better than this.
I'm already planning for next season.
We'll enjoy the celebrations now, of course. A great day for the club and our fans. But we're professionals: I'm already thinking about how we can improve next season.
You were a win away from the title. How does it feel missing out?
You had the title in your grasp today, knowing a win would see you crowned champions. But you've fallen at the final hurdle. What went wrong?
We have to come out of this stronger.
The players are devastated, of course. There's not much to say. We have to respond now and make sure we come out of this stronger. We have to do better next season.
We lacked the winning mentality.
The players have had an amazing season but they weren't strong-minded enough to get over the line. We have to be honest now. Maybe some of them don't have what it takes to be champions.
It wasn't about this game.
Of course this result is a huge disappointment. But we have to be honest with ourselves. We've dropped careless points over the season, and that's why we found ourselves where we were today.
That's a shattering blow. What happened?
That's heart-breaking. A draw would have seen you crowned champions, but your boys have been beaten. What happened? How will you recover from this?
We've learned a lesson here, I think.
Nobody ever said football was easy. This is a massive disappointment, but the lesson we have to take on is clear. We have to improve. Real winners get over the line.
Nobody ever said football was easy. This is a massive disappointment, but the lesson we have to take on is clear. We have to improve. Real winners get over the line.
We've let ourselves down badly today.
I can't believe what I've just witnessed. With so much at stake, we just couldn't cope with the pressure. I know we'll get stick from the media and our fans now. I have to say we'll deserve it.
It's not about what happened today.
We have to be honest with ourselves. We didn't lose the title today. We dropped points in games we should have won all through the season. We put too much pressure on ourselves going into this game.
What a finish. Title winners. How are you feeling?
You couldn't have asked for a more dramatic climax. Last game of the season and you've clinched the title. What does this achievement say about your team?
The boys have been fantastic all season.
It's been an incredible experience and I'm proud that the boys have grabbed the title at the end of it. They've been great all season, and they were great again today.
It's been an incredible experience and I'm proud that the boys have grabbed the title at the end of it. They've been great all season, and they were great again today.
We've done what we set out to do.
We knew what we wanted to achieve this season and now, right at the end, we've managed to do it. I was sure we had the ability to win the league, and today the team has fulfilled its potential.
The hard part starts now.
It's a great achievement and well done to the boys. But we can't sit still. All our challengers will improve. We have to make sure we do, too, if we want to keep this club at the top.
